post_text: Our lunch delivery program begins on Monday, August 31. We will be handing out lunches at several locations. Your child will be able to pick their lunches up at the following times and locations: Dufur Christian Church for all students living in the Dufur City Limits from 11:30 to 12:30; Calvary Baptist Church for students living in The Dalles from 12:00 to 1:00; Celilo School Parking Lot from 12:30 to 1:00. All other students will have their lunches delivered to their homes between 11:30 and 1:00. If you have any questions please feel free to call Josie Turner at (541)980-1977 or the school at (541)467-2509.

Thanks to all that have completed the district survey concerning school re-opening options. The survey will be live until Friday July 10. We have received 132 responses thus far. Your responses are valued and will be an integral part of our planning for a safe re-entry to school in September.

As our plan comes together we will share with you and request your feedback. We are striving to develop options to serve each families comfort level for re-entry to school. Together we will create quality learning options for all Dufur students both onsite and online.

Have a safe weekend!

post_text:
Here is an update we received from ODE: P-EBT benefits issuance is an ongoing process. and timeframes may vary by student. Families of eligible students that have not received their benefits by August 15, 2020 should reach out to DHS using the contact information listed below. The Oregon Department of Education (ODE) is working closely with school districts and the Department of Human Services (DHS) to ensure that P-EBT benefits are issued to eligible students. The benefits will be issued directly from the Department of Human Services. Benefits issuance questions should be directed to DHS by calling (503) 945-6481 or through email at ebt.schoolmeals@dhsoha.state.or.us
ODE Child Nutrition Programs would like to make you aware of the following important resource for accessing additional nutrition in your area now: Needfood.Oregon.gov We would also like to invite you to visit ODE‚Äôs website under the Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer section for information and resources pertaining to P-EBT.

All School Districts in our state are currently working on educational plans for the fall. The Dufur School Districts intent is to be in school as scheduled in late August.

We will be working to develop the required plan for the Oregon Department of Education throughout the summer. The district will be requesting input from the community in the development of the plan.

We plan to begin summer conditioning programs for high school student athletes beginning on July 6.

All dates / times for conditioning opportunities will be announced on June 29.

post_text: An achievement is ‚Äúa thing done successfully, typically by effort, courage, or skill.‚Äù The Agriculture Achievement Award celebrates a student that has done just that in the areas of agriculture, whether that be in Plant or animal science, the shop classes, SAE projects or their participation in FFA. In the last four years they have put in the effort and courage to continually build their skill level and reach out to mentor their fellow classmates. They are responsible, respectful and always pushing themselves to be better, even if that means coming in and working extra hours to make up for time lost. This year I have had the pleasure of awarding this honor to two of our seniors. Getting to watch these students make huge strides and grow into their metaphorical boots has been a real honor and I am so thankful to have been a part of their journey. Please join me in honoring our 2020 Agriculture Achievement Award winners, Jake Dollarhide and Griffin Harrah.

Dufur School Principal Jenny Collins has accepted a High School Principal's position in the Eugene area. Because our current situation doesn't allow the capacity to have a school wide "goodbye" for Mrs. Collins, we have been thinking of another way to send her on her new adventure. If your student and / or family would like to send her a piece of artwork, a note or something else, please take a picture and send it to Bonnie at beverson@dufur.k12.or.us. We will compile it and insure that Mrs. Collins gets it.

Thank you for your two years of service to the Dufur School District, and best of luck with your new position Mrs. Collins!

post_text: Dufur School has decided to proactively begin suspending events that bring large groups of students, adults, and community members together. Suspension of non-essential school-based activities begins immediately, effective March 12- April 10th. Athletic teams will continue to practice, but all extra-curricular activities including athletic competitions will be suspended indefinitely. The after school program will not be suspended at this time. MCT will rehearse tonight, but public performances have been canceled.

Robert Jamack‚ÄéColumbia Gorge Classifieds
January 4 at 12:08 PM ¬∑

The Mid Columbia Umpire Association is looking for new or experienced umpires for both baseball and softball and the upcoming 2020 season. The MCUA provides umpires services to the Mid Columbia Area High Schools. The lack of officials is a crisis that is occurring across the US and it is starting to take a big effect in our local area. Help support and give back to the area in becoming an official so that High School sports can be played. No experience is required. Training will be provided. The association can also assist in the purchase of equipment needed to umpire. There are programs for veterans. Questions please leave a comment or message me directly.

text: The Mid Columbia Umpire Association is looking for new or experienced umpires for both baseball and softball and the upcoming 2020 season. The MCUA provides umpires services to the Mid Columbia Area High Schools. The lack of officials is a crisis that is occurring across the US and it is starting to take a big effect in our local area. Help support and give back to the area in becoming an official so that High School sports can be played. No experience is required. Training will be provided. The association can also assist in the purchase of equipment needed to umpire. There are programs for veterans. Questions please leave a comment or message me directly.
